The fix is complete and clean. Here is a summary of what was done:

---

## Fix: Optimistic remediation assumption on mount

**File changed:** `/Users/thamsanqamoyo/Documents/code/jem-open/jem-sec-attest/app/[tenant]/training/page.tsx` (lines 646-654)

**Problem:** When loading a failed session on mount, the code unconditionally set `evaluateNextAction` to `"remediation-available"`. This caused the "Start Remediation Training" button to be shown even when attempts were exhausted (`attemptNumber >= maxAttempts`), which is incorrect.

**Fix applied:**

```typescript
// Before
// T023: For failed sessions loaded on mount, assume remediation may be available.
// The server will return 409 if remediation is not enabled or attempts are exhausted.
if (derived === "failed-review" && evaluateNextAction === null) {
  setEvaluateNextAction("remediation-available");
}

// After
// T023: For failed sessions loaded on mount, offer remediation only if attempts
// remain. The server is the authority (it returns 409 if remediation is disabled),
// but we avoid showing the button at all when we already know attempts are
// exhausted from the session data.
if (derived === "failed-review" && evaluateNextAction === null) {
  const resolvedMaxAttempts = data.maxAttempts ?? 3;
  if (data.session.attemptNumber < resolvedMaxAttempts) {
    setEvaluateNextAction("remediation-available");
  }
}
```

**Data sources used:**
- `data.session.attemptNumber` — the current attempt number from `TrainingSessionResponse`
- `data.maxAttempts` — returned by the GET `/api/training/{tenant}/session` endpoint (from tenant config), with a fallback of `3` matching the server's own default

**Behavior:**
- If `attemptNumber < maxAttempts` (e.g., attempt 1 of 3, or 2 of 3): sets `"remediation-available"`, showing the "Start Remediation Training" button. The server remains the ultimate authority and will return 409 if remediation is disabled via tenant config.
- If `attemptNumber >= maxAttempts` (attempts exhausted): leaves `evaluateNextAction` as `null`, so the failed-review UI falls through to the exhausted/contact-admin message instead.

The fix is complete and clean. Here is a summary of what was done:

